Description: Fix CVE-2026-34517 — enforce client_max_size during multipart non-file
 field reading instead of after the entire field has been buffered.
 .
 Backport of upstream PR #12216 (commit 9cc4b917 / 3.13 backport cbb774f3) adapted
 for aiohttp 3.12.15. The 3.13 fix uses BodyPartReader.decode_iter (an async
 iterator added in 3.13 via PR #12028/#12035) which is not available in 3.12.
 .
 Adaptation: read the non-file field via field.read_chunk() in a loop, enforce
 client_max_size on each chunk before accumulating, then decode the assembled
 bytes synchronously via field.decode(). For form-data parts, decode() does not
 apply Content-Encoding (compression), so the post-decode size cannot exceed the
 already-checked accumulated size.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/pull/12216
Bug: https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/security/advisories/GHSA-3wq7-rqq7-wx6j
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-06-01

