Description: Fix CVE-2026-54277 - Enforce max_line_size on fragmented request target and reason in C parser
 The C HTTP parser's cb_on_url and cb_on_status callbacks only checked the
 length of the current fragment against max_line_size, allowing an attacker
 to bypass the limit by splitting a long line across multiple TCP reads.
 Each individual fragment can be under the limit while the accumulated line
 grows unbounded, leading to excessive memory consumption (CWE-770).
